## SEO Optimization Rules
### Title Tag Rules
- Include primary keyword within first 60 characters
- Use power words: "Ultimate", "Complete", "Best", "Guide", "Tips"
- Avoid keyword stuffing (maximum 2-3 keywords)
- Include brand name when appropriate
- Create urgency or curiosity when relevant

### Meta Description Rules
- Include primary keyword naturally in first 120 characters
- Use action words: "Learn", "Discover", "Get", "Find", "Master"
- Include clear value proposition
- Add call-to-action when appropriate
- Avoid duplicate content across pages

### Heading Structure Rules
- Single H1 per page with primary keyword
- H2 tags for main sections with secondary keywords
- Use descriptive, keyword-rich headings
- Maintain logical content hierarchy
- Include LSI keywords in subheadings

### Content Optimization Rules
- Natural keyword integration (1-3% density)
- Include LSI keywords for content depth
- Use bullet points and numbered lists for readability
- Include relevant internal links (2-5 per 1000 words)
- Optimize images with alt text and keywords

